22:46.502 --> 22:48.566
And I think I'm goin' crazy.

22:50.838 --> 22:53.810
I've lost it, man.
I think that I am goin' crazy.

22:55.478 --> 22:58.783
You may be.

22:58.845 --> 23:03.005
Your mind may be shot,
but I hope your body isn't.

23:03.089 --> 23:05.946
- Do I get to warm up?
- Yeah.

23:06.018 --> 23:10.188
Two miles any pace you like and then,
uh, let's do ten.

23:10.261 --> 23:13.159
- Ten?
- Too much for ya, huh?

23:13.233 --> 23:15.588
Nah. Not enough.

23:15.662 --> 23:19.759
- I was thinkin' of maybe 20.
- Geez, Bill, you never change.

23:19.842 --> 23:23.065
Why don't we just drop our pants
and see who's got the bigger dick?

23:23.137 --> 23:27.370
- Then we can go back and have a nice, civilized breakfast.
- Wouldn't be civilized.

23:27.475 --> 23:29.403
- Why?
- You'd be sulkin'.

23:29.476 --> 23:31.707
Ahh.

23:31.780 --> 23:34.981
- They don't have hills in New York.
- Hang on a second.

23:35.044 --> 23:37.180
- Huh? What?
- Hang on a second.

23:37.243 --> 23:39.620
Hang on a second here.
What was that?

23:39.683 --> 23:41.611
What the hell
was that?

23:43.686 --> 23:49.483
- What are you afraid of?
- I think I got a gear slippin' here or somethin'.

23:49.566 --> 23:51.609
That's not
what I meant.

23:51.693 --> 23:55.853
What's with the security system, the
security gates, lookin' over your shoulder?

23:55.936 --> 23:59.189
- I been gettin' some threats.
- You mean death threats?

23:59.303 --> 24:01.931
Pretty sure it's somebody
in the Monday night group.

24:02.035 --> 24:04.798
- I just don't know who.
- Monday night as in last night?

24:04.871 --> 24:07.102
Yeah.

24:07.175 --> 24:10.574
I was hopin' maybe with your tuning
fork that you might have a hunch.

24:10.678 --> 24:13.649
No. No hunches, Bob.

24:13.711 --> 24:15.651
What makes you think
it's somebody in the group?

24:15.714 --> 24:20.050
Only about a dozen things. It's been
going on for a couple of months now.

24:20.124 --> 24:22.313
It's funny how it
gets to you after a while.

24:22.386 --> 24:24.252
- You call the cops?
- Yeah.

24:24.315 --> 24:28.557
They said if they had to protect every
shrink in L.A., they'd need an army.

24:28.631 --> 24:31.821
But that I should call 'em
if, uh, anything happens.

24:31.894 --> 24:34.156
Yeah. That makes sense.

24:34.271 --> 24:37.722
Yeah. It'll probably
all just blow over.

24:39.171 --> 24:41.434
- Yeah.
- How 'bout you?

24:41.506 --> 24:43.769
How 'bout me what?

24:43.841 --> 24:47.011
What do you give a suicidal patient
who's got everything?

24:47.074 --> 24:50.514
- A parachute. I heard it already.
- Out here already, huh?

24:50.577 --> 24:52.515
Come on, old-timer.

25:04.255 --> 25:06.246
Oh... shit.

25:06.361 --> 25:10.948
- You may have to...
You may have to carry me in.

25:11.063 --> 25:13.993
You know, you lose
a lot more gracefully than you used to.

25:14.065 --> 25:16.724
Yeah, well, you know,
practice and all.

25:16.807 --> 25:19.268
Hey, how 'bout that?
Learning To Lose, by Dr. Bill Capa.

25:19.330 --> 25:21.270
- Got a ring to it.

25:21.343 --> 25:24.001
They're makin' them seats
a little smaller, huh? Whoo!

25:24.137 --> 25:27.702
I'll see you
next week, all right?

25:27.785 --> 25:30.236
I'm goin' now.
You want me to lock up on the way out?

25:30.308 --> 25:32.248
That'd be great, Barbara.

26:30.203 --> 26:32.133
Just relax.

27:27.919 --> 27:29.818
Barbara?

27:56.643 --> 28:00.572
No!
No-o-o-o!

28:06.880 --> 28:08.819
Why?

29:02.636 --> 29:05.325
- Have you thought about...
- Man, I didn't do nothing.

29:05.430 --> 29:08.965
- Oh, please? You know, you're very cute.
- Yeah, I love you too.

29:09.027 --> 29:11.759
Relax.

29:13.469 --> 29:16.930
- You Capa?
- Yes, I'm Bill Capa.

29:18.285 --> 29:20.214
You're here because
of the dead doctor?

29:22.747 --> 29:24.676
Yes.

29:24.749 --> 29:28.481
Um, I read something
about sessions on Mondays?

29:28.554 --> 29:30.994
Tell me about
this Monday group.

29:32.255 --> 29:34.747
There's five patients
in the group.

29:34.861 --> 29:38.886
- I can't really remember their names right now.
- Like five cuckoos?

29:40.065 --> 29:42.962
No. Four neurotics
of varying degrees...

29:42.993 --> 29:46.059
and one killer.

29:46.142 --> 29:48.394
At least that's
what Bob thought.

29:48.467 --> 29:51.094
- Bob Moore?
- Good. Yes, Bob Moore.

29:51.178 --> 29:54.910
- Uh, four men and one woman.
- Right.

29:56.515 --> 29:59.174
And you sat in on
one of these sessions, right?

29:59.247 --> 30:01.301
Yes, I did.

30:01.384 --> 30:04.710
- So who did it? Hey, hey, hey!

30:04.783 --> 30:07.911
Anderson!
This is civilization, man!

30:08.026 --> 30:10.549
What do you think this is,
your bedroom? Damn!

30:10.653 --> 30:14.823
Knock! Knock! Don't come
into my office like that, bro. Hey!

30:19.765 --> 30:21.735
Whew.

30:21.797 --> 30:25.321
It's a Third World thing.

30:29.168 --> 30:32.702
- Where were we?
- You were probing me about the patients.

30:32.776 --> 30:36.144
I was about to tell you that I really
can't help you. I don't know these people.

30:36.206 --> 30:40.053
But you're a professional, like me.
You gotta have some kind of suspicion.

30:40.147 --> 30:43.775
I really don't have a clue.
I'd like to help you.

30:43.889 --> 30:47.288
Even if I could, there's
an issue of confidentiality.

30:48.894 --> 30:50.875
- Confidentiality?
- Yes.

30:53.085 --> 30:56.463
You're talkin' to me
about an issue of confidentiality?

30:56.525 --> 30:59.059
Similar to
the Miranda oath.

31:00.372 --> 31:02.301
If a friend of mine got killed...

31:02.363 --> 31:05.856
and the only thing between
the killer and me was Miranda...

31:05.940 --> 31:08.838
you know what I would do?

31:08.911 --> 31:10.839
I'd fuck Miranda
up the ass, okay?

31:10.902 --> 31:16.366
But don't tell anybody, because
it's a matter of confidentiality. Shh.

31:16.448 --> 31:18.502
Look, I'm sorry.

31:18.617 --> 31:21.776
I can't help ya. I've only been
in Los Angeles four days.

31:21.860 --> 31:26.227
You're sleeping in that...
dead guy's house, aren't you?

31:26.280 --> 31:28.750
- Yes.
- Maybe something will come to you in the night.

31:28.824 --> 31:34.453
You know, like dreams and shit. What
happens to patients in a situation like this?

31:34.537 --> 31:40.094
Usually a colleague will offer to take
over the group, continue the treatment.

31:40.167 --> 31:43.336
How sweet.
How sweet.

31:43.399 --> 31:46.057
It's like one of
the vultures dies...

31:46.141 --> 31:49.602
and then the others step in line
and eat his portion?

31:49.675 --> 31:51.646
Is that what you're planning?

31:51.708 --> 31:54.648
- No.
- Why not?

31:54.711 --> 31:58.109
- 'Cause I really can't handle that right now.
- Sure you can!

31:58.224 --> 32:03.051
Come on. You've been a week in L.A. You
already have your own private squirrel farm.

32:03.124 --> 32:06.679
How bad can that be?
That's a great career move.

32:06.762 --> 32:10.088
Where were you at the time
of the killing, Capa?

32:11.632 --> 32:13.685
I was at his house...
at Bob's house.

32:13.769 --> 32:16.458
You had to think
about that?

32:16.531 --> 32:19.701
Jesus Christ. You gonna arrest me,
Lieutenant Martinez?

32:19.795 --> 32:22.140
- You want a lawyer?
- Do I need a lawyer?

32:22.234 --> 32:25.435
You're in L.A.
Everybody needs a lawyer.

32:27.207 --> 32:29.104
Ay.

32:30.648 --> 32:35.110
You can go home now. Take a shower.
And keep your mouth shut.

32:35.183 --> 32:38.676
The only thing I got goin' for me
is that few people know what happened.

32:38.758 --> 32:40.813
I don't want the press
fucking things up.

33:09.305 --> 33:11.683
- All right, all right. Hold on.

33:19.189 --> 33:21.118
Oh, shit.

33:24.558 --> 33:28.092
- Capa? Capa, are you there?
- Yeah.

33:28.197 --> 33:30.532
- How's it going?
- What do you want?

33:30.595 --> 33:33.826
I brought the victim's car back,
and I gotta search the house.

33:33.900 --> 33:35.891
You got
a search warrant?

33:36.000 --> 33:41.571
What is it with you? Don't you want
me to find out who killed your friend?

33:41.645 --> 33:44.773
- No, I don't have a warrant.
- All right, come on in.

33:44.857 --> 33:47.257
- Open the gate.
- Yeah, right.

33:47.330 --> 33:50.658
- How's that?

33:51.856 --> 33:53.849
You got the sprinklers on.

33:56.133 --> 33:58.732
How 'bout that?

34:17.206 --> 34:19.898
Jill. His wife.

34:19.971 --> 34:22.538
- His ex-wife.
- Nice bush.

34:24.842 --> 34:26.773
I'll tell her
you said so.

34:29.286 --> 34:31.311
I'm sure it'll mean
a lot to her.

34:33.094 --> 34:35.056
Check this fucking bed.

34:37.058 --> 34:38.998
Damn.

34:42.899 --> 34:45.560
Everybody's having fun
but me, goddamn it.

34:55.888 --> 35:00.947
- I do not like guns.
- You prefer knives?

35:01.031 --> 35:04.004
- I need you to do me a favor.
- What's that?

35:04.078 --> 35:07.593
- I want you to tell the group about Moore's death.
- Me?

35:07.708 --> 35:09.648
- Yes.
- Why?

35:09.711 --> 35:11.682
Well, maybe one of them
won't come in.

35:11.745 --> 35:15.480
Or maybe they would all come in, but then
you would be able to spot something wrong.

35:15.552 --> 35:19.579
- I can't handle it right now.
- I just had all the mess in his office cleaned up.

35:19.663 --> 35:22.792
Don't you want to help me
find the killer? Have a heart.

35:22.865 --> 35:25.661
- What does that mean?
- If you don't tell 'em, I'll have to tell 'em.

35:25.733 --> 35:27.664
Am I the person to break
the news to these people?

35:27.738 --> 35:30.397
"Listen up, you fuckin' daffodils.
Your shrink is dead.

35:30.480 --> 35:35.071
Which means that all the time, effort and
love you put in this relationship is wasted.

35:35.154 --> 35:38.712
You're gonna remain as fucked up
as you are, or get worse."

35:38.794 --> 35:41.778
You are one sinister
piece of work.

35:50.207 --> 35:53.442
All right.
I'll do it.

35:53.504 --> 35:56.143
It's better if you do it.

35:56.206 --> 35:58.343
No, you listen to me.
You don't understand, Gene.

35:58.417 --> 36:00.608
Don't lie. Just give
the family what it wants.

36:00.691 --> 36:02.986
No. No, you don't understand.

36:03.049 --> 36:05.930
- What...?

36:05.992 --> 36:07.921
I have to call ya back.

36:10.570 --> 36:12.511
Christ.

36:13.606 --> 36:15.839
Hey, you all right?

36:15.943 --> 36:18.145
Hey.

36:20.011 --> 36:22.484
Why me?

36:22.577 --> 36:25.718
Hi. I'm Rose.

36:25.790 --> 36:29.880
Hi, Rose. Nice of you
to run into me like this.

36:29.963 --> 36:31.893
I'm Bill Capa.

36:31.967 --> 36:34.397
I got no insurance.

36:36.306 --> 36:39.332
I know it's against the law
and everything.

36:41.513 --> 36:43.712
Don't bust my chops.

36:43.786 --> 36:47.114
I'll bring the money to you, if you
could just get an estimate, okay?

36:47.228 --> 36:50.598
- Why don't you give me a break, huh?
- Got a pen?

36:50.661 --> 36:52.600
Yeah.

37:01.311 --> 37:03.168
- Here.
- Thanks.

37:07.987 --> 37:13.589
Oh. Poor old brain
can't remember its own phone number?

37:13.653 --> 37:16.354
I just moved here.

37:16.428 --> 37:19.484
- Oh.
- From New York.

37:19.599 --> 37:23.510
I wrote my address down
'cause I'm not sure about this number.

37:23.573 --> 37:25.127
I don't know how long
I'm gonna be there...

37:25.242 --> 37:28.581
so maybe you can call me sometime
over the next couple of days.

37:28.653 --> 37:32.210
- I will.
- Bye.

37:32.283 --> 37:35.059
Hey, uh, don't you
want my address?

37:36.957 --> 37:38.960
You could lie.

37:57.122 --> 37:59.116
Hi.

37:59.230 --> 38:02.786
- Who hasn't arrived yet?
- Sondra.

38:02.870 --> 38:05.530
- Where's Bob?
- W-What's wrong?

38:05.605 --> 38:08.702
If it's all right,
I'd rather wait till we're all here.

38:10.612 --> 38:14.920
- She always this late?
- Depends on who is banging her.

38:14.982 --> 38:17.246
I'm sorry.

38:17.330 --> 38:19.884
Class was really,
really, really late.

38:19.958 --> 38:22.785
What class is that? Advanced
cunnilingus for the single woman...

38:22.858 --> 38:25.226
or C.P.R. For
pleasure and gain?

38:25.298 --> 38:28.887
- Oh, Christ. Don't excite her.
- Where's Dr. Moore?

38:29.003 --> 38:31.944
- There's something that I want to tell you.
- What?

38:32.018 --> 38:34.771
Well, what's the matter?

38:34.844 --> 38:37.149
- Yeah?
- Well, I...

38:37.213 --> 38:39.821
I'm tryin' to pay attention. Shh!

38:39.884 --> 38:41.917
You should prepare yourselves
for bad news.

38:41.989 --> 38:44.755
Why? Uh-oh.

38:44.827 --> 38:46.759
Bob's been killed.

38:46.830 --> 38:49.365
- What are you saying?

38:49.429 --> 38:52.308
- What are you telling me?
- He was murdered.

38:52.371 --> 38:54.968
- He was locking up here
late Friday night.

38:55.041 --> 38:57.012
- Here?
- Yes, right here in the office.

38:57.075 --> 39:01.143
Was he shot, stabbed, beaten?
Have they got a suspect? A motive?

39:01.258 --> 39:03.084
Three days go by
and you don't call us?

39:03.187 --> 39:06.087
- I thought it'd be easier if you heard it together.
- Oh, I see.

39:06.161 --> 39:08.092
So even Bob's death
is group therapy. That's great.

39:08.164 --> 39:11.002
Hey, Bob, thanks for giving us
a chance to grieve together. Shit!

39:11.076 --> 39:14.006
- What the fuck is going on? I need to know more!
- He was stabbed to death.

39:14.069 --> 39:17.740
- How many times was he stabbed?
- This man was Bob's best friend!

39:17.814 --> 39:20.745
- Do you really need exact numbers now?
- Sondra!

39:20.818 --> 39:24.115
- Get your fucking hands off me.
- It's okay. It's okay.

39:26.263 --> 39:30.165
- It doesn't make sense to me!
- Many times, Clark.

39:30.228 --> 39:32.700
More than 30.
That's all I can tell you.

39:32.763 --> 39:34.500
It wasn't a thief.
I'll tell you that right now.

39:34.600 --> 39:38.176
- I agree.
- Why stab a guy 30 times?

39:38.249 --> 39:42.079
Bob... He'd piss in his pants if
you showed him a knife. You know that.

39:42.152 --> 39:44.165
- What are you saying?
- I am saying, Sondra...

39:44.248 --> 39:47.983
that you really have to hate a person
to stab him that many times!

39:48.056 --> 39:51.508
You're a shrink, right? You know what
kind of power people hand over to shrinks.

39:51.593 --> 39:54.428
Well, maybe sometimes they hand over
more than they want to.

39:54.502 --> 39:57.068
That is absolutely correct.

39:57.131 --> 40:01.940
A thief would not stick around
to stab someone 30 times.

40:02.004 --> 40:05.007
Since when did you become
such an expert on robbery?

40:05.081 --> 40:08.075
It's not the robbery
he's an expert on. It's the rage.

40:08.189 --> 40:11.590
W- What are we gonna do now?
I- I mean us.

40:11.662 --> 40:16.723
- Th-The group.
- I bet Dr. Capa has an idea.

40:16.796 --> 40:19.529
What does he mean?

40:22.711 --> 40:26.007
I think Casey
is suggesting that I...

40:26.081 --> 40:28.166
may have some plan
to replace Bob.

40:30.181 --> 40:35.448
- Maybe you should.
- No, I can't do that. Not right now.

40:35.522 --> 40:38.150
- Why? Why not?
- For one reason or another...

40:38.233 --> 40:40.633
I'm more screwed up
than you people are.

40:40.737 --> 40:43.001
I was just being
obnoxious and loud before.

40:43.105 --> 40:46.736
- Anybody have a fuckin' Xanax?
- I have a Librium.

40:46.839 --> 40:50.084
- Stop with the drugs.
- It would be a good idea if you stayed.

40:50.147 --> 40:52.338
- Body isn't cold yet.
- There'd be some connection.

40:52.421 --> 40:55.873
You were Bob's best friend.

40:55.958 --> 40:58.680
You... You seem
kind of like him.

40:58.763 --> 41:01.528
It'd be so much easier
to trust you.

41:01.590 --> 41:05.867
I know what kind of a force
group can become in your lives.

41:05.940 --> 41:08.496
You... tell things here.

41:08.580 --> 41:12.032
Intimate things that you wouldn't
tell your best friend.

41:13.482 --> 41:15.538
I'm very flattered
that you would, uh...

41:19.858 --> 41:24.353
But the truth is, you are
the people that make this work.

41:24.436 --> 41:29.194
I will be more than happy to try and find
someone for you to continue this, but I cannot...

41:29.267 --> 41:32.803
Does my opinion
count for anything?

41:32.876 --> 41:34.899
I would like to ask...

41:34.983 --> 41:38.312
why it is you feel
so inadequate for the task.

41:39.824 --> 41:41.754
Maybe he just
don't like us.

41:41.827 --> 41:43.954
- No, that's not it, Buck. - Shh!

41:44.027 --> 41:46.322
Why don't you step on something?

41:52.008 --> 41:55.169
Six weeks ago, I spoke
harshly to a patient...

41:55.242 --> 41:57.140
and she committed suicide.

41:59.779 --> 42:01.709
Right in front of me.

42:05.892 --> 42:10.525
Perhaps she would have done this anyway.
That's what my colleagues say.

42:10.597 --> 42:12.589
But I don't know.

42:12.673 --> 42:15.302
Oh, I'm so sorry.

42:17.576 --> 42:20.769
And my patient...

42:20.852 --> 42:22.814
her name was Michelle...

42:26.955 --> 42:29.731
jumped out of a wi...
window in my office.

42:30.867 --> 42:34.319
- Oh.
- So much blood.

42:35.438 --> 42:38.129
So red, and I...

42:38.212 --> 42:41.269
And right, uh,
before my eyes...

42:41.341 --> 42:45.013
the red, uh,
disappeared.

42:45.086 --> 42:49.885
Just turned to gray, and so
I don't see... red now.

42:51.355 --> 42:54.204
But, see, I was her doctor.

42:54.266 --> 42:57.865
And I failed.
So I can't help you.

42:59.867 --> 43:03.028
I don't think that you want someone
like me around right now.

43:03.112 --> 43:05.304
I think I do.

43:05.385 --> 43:07.546
Me too.

43:07.619 --> 43:10.384
Why don't you give us
a try for a month?

43:10.456 --> 43:13.785
Listen, if you need any...

43:13.857 --> 43:16.924
any free legal advice...

43:16.997 --> 43:19.303
you know, to help
wrap up Bob's affairs...

43:19.376 --> 43:21.306
please don't hesitate
to call me.

43:21.368 --> 43:25.572
I'm not with anyone right now, and I would
be more than happy to help you in any way.

43:29.787 --> 43:31.718
Thank you.

43:48.043 --> 43:50.672
- You bring me a confession?
- Nope.

43:50.744 --> 43:53.143
Well, you win some,
you lose some, huh, Capa?

43:53.216 --> 43:56.951
Listen, maybe it wasn't
one of the group.

43:57.015 --> 43:59.987
Oh, no! He's beginning
to like 'em already!

44:00.061 --> 44:04.797
Your friend Bob Moore deserves
a lot more loyalty than this.

44:04.900 --> 44:07.999
Hey, what is... What are we sitting here
shouting at each other for?

44:08.103 --> 44:10.002
- What is with this place?

44:10.074 --> 44:14.018
I used to work in Narcotics,
and I used to come here a lot.

44:14.081 --> 44:17.283
I probably fucked
and/or arrested...

44:17.347 --> 44:19.318
half of these people's
parents.

44:19.392 --> 44:22.365
- It's a nice place. I like it.
- Makes sense.

44:23.688 --> 44:27.297
Look, I'm sorry
I don't have anything for ya.

44:28.529 --> 44:30.479
I'll see ya around.

44:36.082 --> 44:38.607
- So that's it, huh?
- Yep.

44:38.721 --> 44:40.985
Anything you
wanna tell me?

44:42.424 --> 44:45.219
- No.
- Yeah, it's a four-door, man.

44:45.293 --> 44:48.266
- Well, you better shut the group down.
- Who said I hadn't?

44:48.329 --> 44:50.270
Well, have you
or haven't you?

44:54.671 --> 44:57.770
They asked me to take over the group,
and I couldn't say no.

44:57.843 --> 45:00.753
I figured.

45:00.817 --> 45:03.341
You're gonna do real well
in this town.

